[Student "S"]
{WEST obviously has to pass when SOUTH opens 1\S.

EAST has a reasonable Takeout Double. She hopes WEST will name a suit and they can just 
play a partscore.

You should almost always bid when partner makes a Takeout Double. Almost always. This is the one time 
when you don't. WEST's \S are so good that he passes, converting the Takeout Double into a 
Penalty Double.}

